just_use perf_harness.py

# label: TOOL
# role: profile and benchmark the agent's hot path

The OPTIMIZE_PYTHON instrumentation. Loads find_play
snapshots captured by `agent_game.py --capture FILE`,
benchmarks reproducible (hand, board) cases, runs cProfile
on the slowest one.

## Capture inputs

```
python3 agent_game.py --capture /tmp/perf_snapshots.jsonl ...
```

Each line: `{hand, board, projections, total_wall,
found_play}`. JSON-safe (cards are 3-tuples represented as
lists of ints; restored to tuples by the harness).

## Run

```
python3 perf_harness.py /tmp/perf_snapshots.jsonl
    [--top N]            # show the N slowest cases (default 10)
    [--repeats N]        # how many times to re-time each (default 5)
    [--profile-slowest]  # cProfile the worst case
```

Reports per-case median wall + the per-projection breakdown.
With `--profile-slowest`, dumps cProfile's top-30 cumulative-
time entries for the worst case.

## Pointers

- `agent_game.py` `--capture` flag — the input source.
- `agent_prelude.find_play` — the function under test.
- `bfs.solve_state_with_descs` — the inner BFS.
